This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Thirteenth day of February in the year
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and Sixty nine</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry F Small</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Sarah</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> 
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">John G. Sewall</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joanna</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary S. Goodale</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Ann Elizabeth Camp</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Walter 
D. Sewall</ENAMEX> by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">attorney</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">E. L. Sewall</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Edmund L Sewall</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Kate</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> of the second part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Homer C. Blakeslee</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Olean Cattaraugus County</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
of thed party
Winesseth, That the said party of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Twelve Hundred and Thirty Six Dollars</NUMEX> 
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these presents do grant and convey to the said party of the hind part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX>
and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, ALL those tracts or parcels of land situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Olean</ENAMEX> aforesaid and
described on a map of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Village</ENAMEX> made by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">T. J. Gosseline</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX> as lot number <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">One 
Two, Three, Four, Five, Six, Seven</ENAMEX>, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Eight, Nine, Ten, Eleven, Twelve, Thirteen, fifteen, Seventeen 
Nineteen. Twenty One. and Twenty Three</TIMEX>, and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Twenty Eight</NUMEX> feet off the west end of lots
number <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Fourteen, Sixteen, Eighteen, Twenty</TIMEX><TIMEX TYPE="DATE">, Twenty Two and Twenty Four</TIMEX> in Block Forty
and lots number One, <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Two</NUMEX>, There <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Four</NUMEX>, Five<ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">, Six, Seven, Eight, Nine</ENAMEX>, Ten, Eleven. & <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Twelve</NUMEX>
the Block Forty One. and all of Blocks Fifty <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Five and Fifty Six</NUMEX> Excepting lots One. 
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Two</NUMEX> Three and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Four</NUMEX> in Block Fifty Six, and Excepting also. <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">One Hundred</NUMEX> feet off
the East end of lots <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Two</NUMEX> and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Four</NUMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Block Fifty Five</ENAMEX>, being all of the above described 
lots Except those parts heretofore conveyed by <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two</NUMEX> deeds to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">S. Savage</ENAMEX>, also a strip of land <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twelve</NUMEX> feet wide more or less off the East side of Block number Nine 
Twenty <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Four Thirty nine and Fifty Four</NUMEX> Also <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">14/100</NUMEX> feet in width more or less of
lot number Thirty Nine in Block Eighty <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">four</NUMEX>, Bounded <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">3</NUMEX>, feet from the North bounds
of said lots on the south line of lot heretofore conveyed to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Isabella Brickle</ENAMEX>, and
on the South by lot sold to <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Mrs.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gilligan</ENAMEX> & also lot number Nine in Block 153. and
Also the whole of Block number <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Two</NUMEX>, Twenty <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Five, and Twenty Six</TIMEX>, it being intended hereby 
to convey all such lots and parts of lots, ( together with the interest if any of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary 
C. Sewall</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> in the Streets adjoining said lots, in the said <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of
Olean</ENAMEX> as were the property in fee of the <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> of said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary C. Sewall</ENAMEX> and have not 
been conveyed or contracted to be conveyed by contracts now in force by said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">May 
C. Small</ENAMEX> or <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">representatives</ENAMEX> or <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and only such lots and parts of lots any- to the
thing in the foregoing ⌨⌨ withstanding.
Wh the Bppenances, And all the estate, title and interest therein of the said party of the first part. And the said parties of the
First and second part
do hereby covenant and agree to and with the said party of the other par <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX>__ <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
that the premises thus conveyed
in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said party of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> will forever WARRANT AND
⎬ DEFEND against any person
<ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof.
In <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Wness</ENAMEX> whereo, The parties of the part have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hands and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry F. Sewall</ENAMEX>

February in the year one thousand eight hundred and
Sixty nine</TIMEX> Before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">E. Q. Sewall</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Kate</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known to be the same person described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument orderly acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same; and the sad <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Kate</ENAMEX>
on a private examination by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, apart from <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>, acknowledged that the executed the same freely, and without any fear or compulsion of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX>, and the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">E. 
Q. Sewall</ENAMEX> also <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Karon to</ENAMEX> an to be the <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">attorney</ENAMEX> in fact of the parties of the first part described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within instrument by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Attorney</ENAMEX>
then and there acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX> executed the same as the act and deed of the said parties of the first part, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lysander H. Brown</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Justice Peace</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX> ⎬ SS. <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">I</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Nelson D. Ferguson</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Clerk</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Jefferson</ENAMEX>, and of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Court of Record</ENAMEX> for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said County</ENAMEX>, do hereby <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">Steven County Clerks Office</ENAMEX> ⎬ Certify that <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Spander H. Brown</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esquire</ENAMEX>, whose name is subscribed to the certificate of proof or acknowledge ment of the annexed instrument and thereon written was at the time of taking such proof or acknowledgment a <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Justice</ENAMEX> of the Price in and for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said County</ENAMEX> residing in the <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said County</ENAMEX>, duly authorized to take the same, that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">I</ENAMEX> am well acquainted with the handwriting of the 
said justice, and verily believe that the signature to the said certificate of proof or acknowledgment is genuine, and that the said 
instrument is executed and acknowledged according to the laws of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>.
In Testimony Whereof, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">I</ENAMEX> have hereunto subscribed <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">my</ENAMEX> name, and affixed the seal of the <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said County and Courts</ENAMEX>
thereof at <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Watertown</ENAMEX> this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">19th day of February 1869</TIMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">H. Hanford</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Dep Clerk</ENAMEX>
